fields.descriptive_line: Manuscript Astasahasrika Prajnaparamita Sutra in Tibetan
fields.physical_description: Manuscript comprised of two carved and gilt pinewood covers, three title pages with brocade guards, 320 blue paper pages of gold text on a polished ground, and a light black wood frame to act as guard to one of the title pages. The upper cover is carved in high relief with the Triratna, Buddhas and Bodhisattvas, celestial attendants and mythical animals amid scrolling foliations. The under cover is in low relief with an Amrita-vase and diaper of interlacing scrolling stems. Each page is protected with a double flap of green and terra-cotta silk.
fields.dimensions: Length: 68 cm approx, Width: 27.5 cm approx, Height: 20 cm approx

fields.historical_context_note: The title of the book means The Prajna Paramita in 8000 slokas. It contains an abbreviated version of the large work and is intended for the use of the general body of the Lamas. It is the book which is one of the lotus-borne symbols of the Bodhisattva Manjushri, the deity of  Transcendent Wisdom.
